FT  06 SEP 93 / Construction Contracts: Restoring holy building
METADALIC, part of the CP Group based in Hayes, has been awarded a contract
worth in the region of Pounds 200,000 to supply materials and full technical
support to the gold plating of a new dome on the famous Dome of the Rock
mosque (pictured above) in the old City of Jerusalem.
The restoration of the dome, worth in the region of Pounds 5m, is proceeding
to schedule with completion expected in December.
